# napi-rs build artifacts — platform-specific, rebuilt by CI.
*.node
node_modules/

# Generated glue (`index.js`, `index.d.ts`) IS committed — it
# changes only when napi config (binary name, targets, exports)
# changes, so it's stable across normal Rust edits, and committing
# it means CI's publish-npm step doesn't need a Rust toolchain to
# regenerate it. Regenerate locally + commit when napi config
# changes:
#   pnpm exec napi build --platform --release \
#     --manifest-path ../../Cargo.toml --package tidepool-node
